description: Davin Loh gets asked a lot about pinballs within the interview, but he is more into arcade systems. Davin is a well known player at the Galloping Ghost arcade, hitting high scores and beating world records. Davin Loh is known within the community to be the best at a handful of games at the arcade, but the biggest one is "Capcom vs SNK 2". A fighting arcade game that puts two players against each other and fights with a 48 character roster, but it's not the multiplayer part he is known for. Davin focuses more on the single player mode, it pins the player to do countless battles against CPUs and then gets awarded points for a score and the more the player wins the higher the points, but the harder the fights become. He brings alot of attention to the arcade when he is attempting to break a record or high score, he has been such a positive player to have at the Galloping Ghost arcade.

description: Doc Mack gets interviewed about his arcade which still holds the title for the worlds largest arcade collection. He has about 885+ arcade games within his collection and contunios to grow with his  time spend searching for titles he wants and the ones the community would like to play. His arcade is free to play, coinless businnes because he doesnt want his customers to limit themselvs on the games they want to play. Rather paying a fee up front for the day and letting gamers have a chnace to expiernce new games with no penalty of running out of coins.

description: George Spanos is one of the great arcade repairmen in Chicago. He has repaired many arcade machines for many top arcades within Chicago such as Underground Retrocade, Pixel Blast Arcade and Galloping Ghost Arcade. He has written many articles on board games, monitors, supplies, etc. but his main focus is repairing these machines since each arcade system holds history in the coin-op era of gaming and holds a place in his childhood.

description: An interview by Ricky Nguyen and Jeremy Chionglo who talk with Sean Davis the director of operations at Lucky Strike. Sean mentions how he has a long history of entertainment business and he wanted to incorporate it more into Lucky Strike. Hence why there are a wide range of different areas of entertainment within Lucky Strike. From arcades that make adults feel like kids again to mini golf themed as historical parts of Chicago. His goal is to make a place where its for the family and not just for the kids or just for the parents.

description: An interview by Douglas Rubio and James Atkins who talk to Rich Huff, who owns Midwest Pinball. Midwest Pinball does not work commercially and is more structured to help residential customers who need repairs on their pinball machines. Rich's experience of being a repairman helps bring life back into these old beaten down machines, so their history would not be forgotten.
